## 2  Reinvestment Scorecard (`reinvestment-scorecard.astro`)

<h1>The Reinvestment Scorecard</h1>

### Purpose  
The scorecard asks: **“Are resource rents being converted into future-proof assets?”** It aggregates five metrics:

| Metric | High | Moderate | Low |
|--------|------|----------|-----|
| **Sustainable CapEx share** (renewables, circular economy, etc.) | > 30 % | 10–30 % | < 10%<sup>[1]</sup> |
| **Reserve-Replacement Ratio** | > 120 % | 80–120 % | < 80%<sup>[2]</sup> |
| **Reinvestment Rate** (CapEx / OCF) | > 100 % | 50–100 % | < 50%<sup>[3]</sup> |
| **Carbon-transition progress** | Net-zero ≤ 2040, Scope-3 plan | Net-zero 2050 | No credible plan<sup>[4]</sup> |
| **Social & human capital spend** | Rising, impact based | Stable | Falling |

### Case snapshot

Freeport-McMoRan scored *Low* on diversification (< 5 % green CapEx), Anglo *High* on reserve replacement (Quellaveco copper), Ørsted *High* across the board after exiting fossil fuels<sup>[5]</sup>.

> Firms that rank *Low* are effectively “eating the seed corn” and would face a **larger user-cost deduction** in sustainable accounts<sup>[6]</sup>.

